Becoming increasingly concerned, Mrs Pott frantically worked the lock from the outside and eventually opened the door. But it was too late - she saw her daughter hanging inside the room.

She wracked her memory for what could have happened to her daughter. She said she remembered seeing marker on her daughter's chest - which the girl quickly dismissed - after the party, and that her daughter had called her unusually early the night after the party to come and collect her.

After the death, Saratoga police agreed with the school to wait until a week later to start an investigation to allow the students time to grieve.

But just days later, Audrie's friend Kathy went to talk to school administrators to explain what she knew about the party and the pictures of her friend.

When police arrived to interview students, there had already been rumors of an investigation and some students were heard urging others to shut down their Facebook accounts, Rolling Stone reported.

